# One concern per branch

Never mix unrelated features, fixes, refactors, or chores on the same branch or in the same PR.

- One branch = one purpose (e.g. `bugfix/exchange-perf` **or** `bugfix/remove-copa-fifa-screenshots`, not both).
- If mid-task you discover separate work, stop and open a new branch from the appropriate base.
- Do not commit marketing/docs/tooling changes alongside app runtime fixes unless they are required for that same fix.
- Prefer `feature/…`, `bugfix/…`, `chore/…`, `docs/…` names that match the single concern.

```text
❌ BAD
bugfix/remove-copa-fifa-screenshots
  + screenshot copy updates
  + Exchange drag performance rewrite
  + share-sheet ImageRenderer cache

✅ GOOD
bugfix/remove-copa-fifa-screenshots   → screenshots / marketing only
bugfix/exchange-drag-performance     → Repetidas perf only
```

Before committing or opening a PR, confirm every changed file serves that branch’s one purpose. If not, split.
